&gt;&gt; Jason Beardsley:
Yeah, I'll try to make it

00:45:19.820 --> 00:45:21.120
as boring as possible.

00:45:21.120 --> 00:45:23.500
Not, very excited,
the VA Mission Act

00:45:23.500 --> 00:45:27.020
that just got passed is one
of the most expansive acts.

00:45:27.020 --> 00:45:30.680
It's appropriated $5.2 billion.

00:45:30.680 --> 00:45:33.930
Part of that too is
expanding on caregivers.

00:45:33.930 --> 00:45:39.190
So we recently, or legacy
caregivers were only post 9/11,

00:45:39.190 --> 00:45:41.500
so we've now rolled that back to
those who have been giving care

00:45:41.500 --> 00:45:44.870
to veterans from the Vietnam
era and the Gulf War era.

00:45:44.870 --> 00:45:46.920
And it's a recognition
on the VA's part

00:45:46.920 --> 00:45:49.680
that we did have a gap
in the environment.

00:45:49.680 --> 00:45:51.790
I think you mentioned,
Steve, that the study

00:45:51.790 --> 00:45:55.140
that Rand did told us
about what's happening

00:45:55.140 --> 00:45:56.910
with our veterans, our
younger population,

00:45:56.910 --> 00:45:58.370
how we're bringing them home,

00:45:58.370 --> 00:46:00.150
and then how we can
actually care for them

00:46:00.150 --> 00:46:02.390
in their homes rather
than facility.

00:46:02.390 --> 00:46:05.180
So part of the VA Mission
Act will help close the loop

00:46:05.180 --> 00:46:06.480
on that.

00:46:06.480 --> 00:46:09.790
In addition, there are so
many other good parts to it,

00:46:09.790 --> 00:46:13.710
but electronic health care
modernization, this is an effort

00:46:13.710 --> 00:46:16.620
for the VA to do what I
think is a common sense,

00:46:16.620 --> 00:46:21.310
modern technology thing, right,
by allowing the service member

00:46:21.310 --> 00:46:24.150
to step into the, you
know, once you swear in,

00:46:24.150 --> 00:46:27.360
you have a service record, and
that record will be electronic

00:46:27.360 --> 00:46:29.710
and will carry with you
for the life of you,

00:46:29.710 --> 00:46:33.630
including when you leave your
service and enter the arms

00:46:33.630 --> 00:46:34.960
of the Department of the VA.

00:46:34.960 --> 00:46:37.720
Right now that's a legacy
system we're dealing

00:46:37.720 --> 00:46:41.830
with that has great features
to it, but it was built 20

00:46:41.830 --> 00:46:44.450
and 30 years ago, so we're
now at the phase where we're

00:46:44.450 --> 00:46:46.670
about to initiate
a change in that,

00:46:46.670 --> 00:46:51.010
which will hopefully
facilitate a lot more care

00:46:51.010 --> 00:46:54.780
with a lot more speed
if you will now.

00:46:54.780 --> 00:46:57.760
The veteran who has his
record, carries it with him,

00:46:57.760 --> 00:47:00.550
and then can share that
out whether it's internal

00:47:00.550 --> 00:47:02.920
to our community or
as importantly now,

00:47:02.920 --> 00:47:04.550
especially with the
VA Mission Act,

00:47:04.550 --> 00:47:07.100
external to our community
care partners.

00:47:07.100 --> 00:47:09.540
And that's another
component of the Mission Act,

00:47:09.540 --> 00:47:14.040
which is we found that
where the VA does well is

00:47:14.040 --> 00:47:15.590
when you get in the door.

00:47:15.590 --> 00:47:18.390
It's when you can't get in that
we have to service our veterans.

00:47:18.390 --> 00:47:21.020
So allowing veterans
to choose their care

00:47:21.020 --> 00:47:23.390
in the community has been a
vital piece, and that's going

00:47:23.390 --> 00:47:25.260
to happen with this as well.

