in the room and those watching

00:49:02.100 --> 00:49:05.040
that less than one-half
of one percent

00:49:05.040 --> 00:49:08.640
of our country is defending our
freedom in the armed services,

00:49:08.640 --> 00:49:11.640
which means there's
99 percent of us

00:49:11.640 --> 00:49:14.450
who don't really understand
what happens inside

00:49:14.450 --> 00:49:16.960
of military families
and the challenges

00:49:16.960 --> 00:49:18.300
that have been discussed up here

00:49:18.300 --> 00:49:20.140
and that are happening
every day.

00:49:20.140 --> 00:49:22.330
And so I'd like to
remind everybody

00:49:22.330 --> 00:49:27.350
that our job really is
only just beginning.

00:49:27.350 --> 00:49:30.440
The veterans who are
continuing to come home

00:49:30.440 --> 00:49:32.490
from the longest period of war

00:49:32.490 --> 00:49:36.880
in U.S. history are bringing
complex needs and issues

00:49:36.880 --> 00:49:40.250
to the home front, and they
have a family and community

00:49:40.250 --> 00:49:44.480
around them that need to
be embraced and supported.

00:49:44.480 --> 00:49:49.250
And it's up to all of us
to ask what we can do.

00:49:49.250 --> 00:49:53.150
So inside of our
employers and our churches,

00:49:53.150 --> 00:49:56.540
our community organizations
and our neighborhoods,

00:49:56.540 --> 00:50:00.950
seek out your military
family neighbors.

00:50:00.950 --> 00:50:04.660
They're, Sam and Steven would
probably say they're reluctant

00:50:04.660 --> 00:50:06.410
to ask for help.

00:50:06.410 --> 00:50:11.690
But if you find them and you
offer, usually they'll take you

00:50:11.690 --> 00:50:14.030
up on it, and sometimes
it's the simple things.

00:50:14.030 --> 00:50:18.220
We know, for instance, most of
our families just need a break.

00:50:18.220 --> 00:50:20.580
Babysitter, cut the lawn,
help with the groceries,

00:50:20.580 --> 00:50:22.020
those sorts of things.

00:50:22.020 --> 00:50:26.470
But it's really up to each of
us to seek out those neighbors,

00:50:26.470 --> 00:50:29.800
friends, family members, and
see what we can do to help them.

