00:51:09.430 --> 00:51:11.260
that still are in need

00:51:11.260 --> 00:51:13.580
and really deserve
these kind of homes.

00:51:13.580 --> 00:51:15.820
So we've got a lot
of work to do.

00:51:15.820 --> 00:51:19.160
The second thing I'd say
for the staffers and members

00:51:19.160 --> 00:51:21.740
that may have tuned in or
will tune in and watch this

00:51:21.740 --> 00:51:28.260
over in the coming days, is we
discussed some of those things

00:51:28.260 --> 00:51:34.230
with the SEH program,
the grant program,

00:51:34.230 --> 00:51:37.490
that needs some changing
to bring some work,

00:51:37.490 --> 00:51:38.830
we're leaving some
veterans behind

00:51:38.830 --> 00:51:40.270
in that program right now.

00:51:40.270 --> 00:51:45.120
So I would ask them to go
back and support the efforts

00:51:45.120 --> 00:51:48.350
of the subcommittee on economic
opportunity as they move forward

00:51:48.350 --> 00:51:49.650
with that with the VA.

00:51:49.650 --> 00:51:56.570
And then last, I would also
say for both my cohorts here

00:51:56.570 --> 00:52:00.300
in other charities, both
mentioned about, you know,

00:52:00.300 --> 00:52:03.290
volunteering, helping
out, and you don't have

00:52:03.290 --> 00:52:06.410
to wear a uniform to be serving.

00:52:06.410 --> 00:52:10.000
All charities out there,
all of us need volunteers.

00:52:10.000 --> 00:52:12.910
We won't succeed
without our volunteers.

00:52:12.910 --> 00:52:16.220
So get online, check us
out, and get out there

00:52:16.220 --> 00:52:17.520
and help these veterans.

00:52:17.520 --> 00:52:18.820
Thanks.

00:52:18.820 --> 00:52:20.120
&gt;&gt; Karen Lloyd: Well said.

00:52:20.120 --> 00:52:21.420
Steve.

00:52:21.420 --> 00:52:23.980
&gt;&gt; Steven Curry: I'll hit on
