00:52:28.650 --> 00:52:35.640
is really built on a combination
of organizations like the VA

00:52:35.640 --> 00:52:39.470
and all of the different
veteran service organizations.

00:52:39.470 --> 00:52:44.520
So, if you know of a
program that the VA offers

00:52:44.520 --> 00:52:51.370
or veteran service out there
that could help out a veteran

00:52:51.370 --> 00:52:55.510
that you know or in
you family, it really,

00:52:55.510 --> 00:52:58.860
it's a really good idea to
given them a push, you know,

00:52:58.860 --> 00:53:01.560
give them a kick in the
rear to go and reach

00:53:01.560 --> 00:53:02.860
out to those organizations.

00:53:02.860 --> 00:53:04.900
Because like I said before, I
would not have applied to Homes

00:53:04.900 --> 00:53:08.220
for Our Troops or I wouldn't
have applied for the SAH grant

00:53:08.220 --> 00:53:11.180
if Sam hadn't have kind of--

00:53:11.180 --> 00:53:12.480
&gt;&gt; Samantha Curry: Pestered you?

00:53:12.480 --> 00:53:16.500
&gt;&gt; Steven Curry: Yeah, guided
me in that direction multiple,

00:53:16.500 --> 00:53:21.120
you know, over a
long period of time.

00:53:21.120 --> 00:53:23.020
And, you know, really
I would have been,

00:53:23.020 --> 00:53:26.610
I would have been missing out,
and I've talked to veterans

00:53:26.610 --> 00:53:31.850
who have that mindset where,
you know, I'll let the guys

00:53:31.850 --> 00:53:36.110
that need it most
access that care,

00:53:36.110 --> 00:53:43.280
and while that's an admirable
thing to think and feel,

00:53:43.280 --> 00:53:46.850
you really should leave it up
to the organizations to decide

00:53:46.850 --> 00:53:48.250
who needs that care the most.

00:53:48.250 --> 00:53:53.040
And on top of that,
like Tom said, you know,

00:53:53.040 --> 00:53:57.880
look at those veteran service
organizations, do your research,

00:53:57.880 --> 00:54:01.920
