00:54:18.240 --> 00:54:19.540
&gt;&gt; Samantha Curry: Definitely.

00:54:19.540 --> 00:54:20.840
Thank you.

00:54:20.840 --> 00:54:22.140
&gt;&gt; Karen Lloyd: And
your thoughts?

00:54:22.140 --> 00:54:23.440
&gt;&gt; Samantha Curry: I
would definitely just say

00:54:23.440 --> 00:54:28.280
to any caregiver out there
find somebody who can be there

00:54:28.280 --> 00:54:30.490
to support you if you need it.

00:54:30.490 --> 00:54:34.000
Or maybe if you know a caregiver
and maybe you're not one

00:54:34.000 --> 00:54:36.800
but you know one, always just
ask them how they're doing,

00:54:36.800 --> 00:54:38.100
do they need something.

00:54:38.100 --> 00:54:40.570
They'll probably be
like me and say no,

00:54:40.570 --> 00:54:41.990
but I think that
they'll understand

00:54:41.990 --> 00:54:45.270
that somebody is still there
and someone still cares

00:54:45.270 --> 00:54:47.920
and is asking how
they're doing for sure.

00:54:47.920 --> 00:54:50.040
&gt;&gt; Karen Lloyd: If somebody
asks you what you needed

00:54:50.040 --> 00:54:51.770
and your tendency is to say no,

00:54:51.770 --> 00:54:56.920
what's the one thing they could
do that would brighten your day?

00:54:56.920 --> 00:55:00.000
&gt;&gt; Samantha Curry: I
think really for me is,

00:55:00.000 --> 00:55:02.100
I think just them asking,
even though I say no,

00:55:02.100 --> 00:55:07.680
just that they will ask,
initiate and ask a question,

00:55:07.680 --> 00:55:10.640
or even if it's just
asking how are you doing

00:55:10.640 --> 00:55:17.260
or how's the family, I think
just asking for me is much more

00:55:17.260 --> 00:55:19.470
than anything than not asking.

00:55:19.470 --> 00:55:24.190
I think that even goes with
saying like an injured veteran,

00:55:24.190 --> 00:55:26.240
you know, don't just
stare at them.

00:55:26.240 --> 00:55:29.980
Most of them will be willing to
talk about it, even if it's just

00:55:29.980 --> 00:55:31.780
like I'm okay, but just ask.

00:55:31.780 --> 00:55:33.080
Definitely just always ask.

00:55:33.080 --> 00:55:35.270
&gt;&gt; Karen Lloyd: That's really
good advice, thank you.

00:55:35.270 --> 00:55:36.570
Jason.

