Yeah, thank you.

00:55:37.870 --> 00:55:39.190
These have been incredible
comments, and so, you know,

00:55:39.190 --> 00:55:42.320
I have to commend the panel.

00:55:42.320 --> 00:55:45.740
I think it's been said, and
I'll emphasize it, you know,

00:55:45.740 --> 00:55:49.120
we don't serve as
single members.

00:55:49.120 --> 00:55:52.090
We serve as families and
really as communities

00:55:52.090 --> 00:55:56.220
because when we put service
members in war or in conflict,

00:55:56.220 --> 00:55:58.540
we do that as a community.

00:55:58.540 --> 00:56:01.600
So knowing that, when
the service members leave

00:56:01.600 --> 00:56:03.510
and come back to
reintegrate in society,

00:56:03.510 --> 00:56:06.090
they can only be
reintegrated also

00:56:06.090 --> 00:56:09.460
by community, family, and peers.

00:56:09.460 --> 00:56:11.460
And it's been said a bunch
of times, but if you're

00:56:11.460 --> 00:56:15.870
out there listening, again, I'll
just say, like Steve, myself,

00:56:15.870 --> 00:56:19.950
and the peers that I served
with, those in harm's way,

00:56:19.950 --> 00:56:22.630
they're mission focused and
they're mission oriented,

00:56:22.630 --> 00:56:25.970
and they're typically the
last ones to say, you know,

00:56:25.970 --> 00:56:28.390
pay attention to me
or give me the care.

00:56:28.390 --> 00:56:32.500
So we do rely on our spouses
and those who are our peers

00:56:32.500 --> 00:56:35.250
to kick us in the gut a
little bit and get us moving.

00:56:35.250 --> 00:56:36.620
So if you know folks like that,

00:56:36.620 --> 00:56:40.210
just know there's an
initial resistance.

00:56:40.210 --> 00:56:42.200
But at the other end,
in the community,

00:56:42.200 --> 00:56:46.120
are these tremendous
organizations, businesses,

00:56:46.120 --> 00:56:50.710
charities, VSOs, MSOs,
that are ready to support.

00:56:50.710 --> 00:56:52.780
And right behind that
is your government.

00:56:52.780 --> 00:56:55.500
We brought you into service,

00:56:55.500 --> 00:56:57.610
we're going to continue
to care for you.

00:56:57.610 --> 00:57:00.190
Sometimes it's a little
difficult figuring out the path

00:57:00.190 --> 00:57:01.870
or navigating that path,

00:57:01.870 --> 00:57:03.710
but that's what we're
all up here for.

00:57:03.710 --> 00:57:05.620
You're not there alone.

00:57:05.620 --> 00:57:09.070
So if anybody hears this message
out there and feels that way,

00:57:09.070 --> 00:57:11.340
it's time for them to kind
of tap out and say, hey,

00:57:11.340 --> 00:57:14.470
I need a hand, and you've
got plenty of people ready

00:57:14.470 --> 00:57:18.490
to help you, and at the end
of that, the organizations,

00:57:18.490 --> 00:57:21.210
the Veterans Affairs
Department, are all here

00:57:21.210 --> 00:57:22.650
to support our veterans.

00:57:22.650 --> 00:57:25.590
So, make sure if you do know
someone, ask the question,

00:57:25.590 --> 00:57:27.900
and then follow up and
get them into the hands

00:57:27.900 --> 00:57:29.890
of that next level of care.

